gomodel:SYNGO_580  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Complexin-2 presynaptic immunoreactivity is observed in the Calyx of Held synapse in the brainstem (Fig 11C).\n\nIHC was performed using an antibody (SySy, rabbit anti-Cplx-1/2) that detects Complexin-1 and -2. Complexin-1 KO mice exhibit a loss of immunoreactivity in the somata of the MNTB principal neurons (Fig 11C) indicating the specificity of the antibody for Complexin-1, however immunoreactivity in the presynaptic terminal persist at P7 indicating the presence of Complexin-2.. Experimental description: Cplx1+/+ and Cplx1-/- littermates of either sex were used for most of the experiments..." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" ;
        dc:date           "2017-05-31" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_580" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

